# Optional. Only needed for custom tooling; static export uses same-origin /api/v1.
# For next dev, `fetch` to /api/v1 is rewritten to the Go API (see next.config.ts).
# Use the SAME base URL for both lines when Go is not on :8080, then restart `npm run dev`:
#   DLM_BACKEND_ORIGIN=http://127.0.0.1:8000
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_DLM_API_ORIGIN=http://127.0.0.1:8000
#
# SSE (EventSource) cannot use that rewrite — Next buffers streams. The UI connects directly
# to Go in development (see web/lib/sseUrl.ts). Defaults to http://127.0.0.1:8080 when unset.
#
# Cross-origin EventSource requires CORS on the Go server. The Go binary defaults to
# http://localhost:3000 and http://127.0.0.1:3000 when CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS is unset.
# Override if you use another port, e.g.:
#   CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=http://localhost:3001 go run ./cmd/server
